The page [http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Restoring+Passwords+To+Recover+Admin+User+Rights] does not reflect the atlassian-user data model for user management. Users of Confluence 2.7.x will find the tables mentioned in the doc empty. User data is now stored in tables _users, groups, local_members_. The sql queries need updating plus a a hint is needed on how to determine whether the Confluence instance uses Open Symphonie or Atlassian-User.
The sql query for a-user is {code}select name from users u, groups g, local_members ug where u.id = ug.userid and g.id = ug.groupid and g.groupname = 'confluence-administrators';{code}

Thank you.

