In the {{atlassian-plugin.xml}} plugin descriptor, it's possible to have an {{application-version}} tag which stores the range of versions for which the plugin works:

{code:xml}
    <plugin-info>
        <description>Tracks usage events in Confluence.</description>
        <vendor name="Atlassian Software Systems Pty Ltd" url="http://www.atlassian.com"/>
        <version>0.7.3-SNAPSHOT</version>
        <application-version min="2.6" max="2.7"/>
    </plugin-info>
{code}

This range (2.6 to 2.7 above) is not displayed in the plugin info, in Confluence's admin section. As it sometimes comes in useful, it should be displayed (as it is in JIRA).

